reviews.text: I chaperoned a trip here for my daughter's school. GREAT EXPERIENCE. Packed with great history and lots of information. The tour guides were spectacular. The whole boat had interesting things to see.  What a great gem for the Kitsap Peninsula to have!

This is a great place to visit! Loaded with history and a fun way to experience being on a ship. My 3- year old did okay getting around, but if you have issues with climbing up and down, or being in tight spaces, this may not be worth going to. You can see a good amount of the ship without climbing, but you will miss a lot if you are uncomfortable with ladders and climbing.

Nice museum and great self-guided tour of the decommissioned destroyer.  You can walk around the majority of the ship at your pace. Highly recommend! The only real challenge will be finding parking as this is not a tourist friendly town!

Great tour! It definitely worth it. I took my Navy buddy that is from out of town to this ship. We both enjoyed it.Both of us are Veterans. It’s great the keep this ship restored so the public and veterans can enjoy it!!

This type of thing is rare, so if you’re in Bremerton definitely go see it. It can be a bit hard to maneuver around inside, especially with ladders, and doors off the ground, so be aware. They have it amazingly maintained. It’s very fun to get lost inside and see everything there is to see!
Great race track for 8th mile. Great community
Great place to run and watch fast cars
Great facility fun for the boys and myself track is safe a and fast!!

It was okay my husband really enjoyed it there's a lot of nice cars racing and they did have bleachers to sit on for me personally it was not something that I would want to do on a regular basis having little ones now as they get older that could change for the older people who like to look at nice cars and watch them go very fast this is the place to be
Safe place to race.
We had a large group and enjoyed the island very much while we camped for 5 days!  Paul is the best ranger! Cheers!

We came to the island for a cruise, dinner and performance. The staff on the cruise and the island were all welcoming. The island is beautiful & wonderfully quite. The trip as a whole was wonderful and being caught in a thunderstorm on the way back was mystical!

I like how it is surrounded by water. I just can't get this at any other park. That is why this one is special. I like feeling trapped by natures most vicious element, salt water. You see I'm deathly allergic to water. That's why I don't exist.
You can pay for a boat to take you, or take your own boat. Indian Village on Island on the western Puget Sound. Easy access from the east side of the sound.
Quiet and beautiful park. Camped one night and hiked around the island. Highly recommended.

Amazing place to camp. Lots of fun things to do with spectacular views. 
There is a great playground and live falcon shows. Paths to ride bikes and  bathrooms and picnic tables. 
Group camping areas. Fun for the whole family.

Beautiful park right on Puget Sound. 27 RV sites that can be reserved, but check the size of the space, many can't take really big rigs. Large grassy day use and tent area. Playground for the kids and great beach for walking. Views of the Sound, Ballard, and Capitol Hill. Would love to stay here again!

Another beautiful park on the shores of Puget Sound.  This one has spots for RV's and tents plus several cabins that looked pretty nice for a rustic waterfront experience.  The view is across the Sound to the north side of Seattle.  Didn't seem to have any long walking trail but nice beach strewn with many driftwood tree trunks.
Very beautiful place and beach. Stunning views of the island. Have a great time with family.
Good beach for beachcombing nice picnic area clean and well cared grounds.
A fun place to ride dirt bikes. Technical trails and lots of great views.
